SCHWEND, INC., a Florida for-profit corporation, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Manuel ZURITA, in his individual capacity, Clyde Lo Chin, in his individual capacity, Julia Diaz, in her individual capacity, Defendants-Appellees. No. 11-10935

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Oct. 13, 2011. Joseph Elton Blitch, Kevin C. Maxwell, Private Counsel, LLC, Orlando, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellant. Michelle Thresher Taylor, Esq., David Paul Rhodes, Erik Kenneth Stegeby, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Tampa, FL, for Defendant-Appellee. Before TJOFLAT, MARCUS and FAY, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

We conclude that the appellees are entitled to the defense of qualified immunity as a matter of law for the reasons stated in the district court’s February 18, 2011 order granting appellees’ motion for summary judgment.

AFFIRMED.
